{{Infobox Military Conflict |image= |caption= |conflict=Battle of Prešov |partof=[[Great Turkish War]] |date=August 11, 1685 |place=[[Prešov|Eperjes]], [[Kingdom of Hungary]] (modern-day Prešov, eastern [[Slovakia]]) |result=Austrian victory |combatant1={{flag|Holy Roman Empire}} |combatant2={{flagicon|Ottoman Empire|1453}}[[Ottoman Empire]] |commander1=General Schulz |commander2=[[Imre Thököly]] |strength1= |strength2= |casualties1= |casualties2= |}} {{Campaignbox Great Turkish War}}
The '''Battle of Eperjes''' (now: ''Prešov'') was fought on August 11, 1685, near the city of [[Prešov|Eperjes]] in the [[Kingdom of Hungary]], between the forces of the [[Ottoman Empire]], and the forces of the [[Holy Roman Empire]] as part of the [[Great Turkish War]]. The Habsburg army defeated the invading forces of [[Imre Thököly]].<ref>{{cite book|title=The Cambridge Modern History|url=http://www.uni-mannheim.de/mateo/camenaref/cmh/cmh512.html|volume=VOLUME V. The Age Of Louis XIV.|chapter=CHAPTER XII. AUSTRIA, POLAND, AND TURKEY.}}</ref>
